Using a standard normal distribution table, we look up the probabilities corresponding to $Z_{lower} = -1.50$ and $Z_{upper} = 0.50$. $P(Z \leq 0.50)$ and $P(Z \leq -1.50)$ are needed.

## Step 8: Look up $P(Z \leq 0.50)$ and $P(Z \leq -1.50)$
$P(Z \leq 0.50) \approx 0.6915$ and $P(Z \leq -1.50) \approx 0.0668$.

## Step 9: Calculate $P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453)$
$P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453) = P(-1.50 \leq Z \leq 0.50) = P(Z \leq 0.50) - P(Z \leq -1.50) = 0.6915 - 0.0668 = 0.6247$.

