The formula for the union of two events is $P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B)$. Substituting the given values, we have $0.92 = P(A) + P(B) - 0.28$.

## Step 4
Simplifying the equation from Step 3 gives $0.92 + 0.28 = P(A) + P(B)$, which simplifies to $1.2 = P(A) + P(B)$.

