## Step 7
Dividing both sides of the equation from Step 6 by 2 gives $P(B) = 1.04 / 2 = 0.52$.

## Step 8
Now that we have $P(B)$, we can find $P(A)$ using the equation $P(A) = P(B) + 0.16$. So, $P(A) = 0.52 + 0.16$.

## Step 9
Calculating $P(A)$ gives $P(A) = 0.52 + 0.16 = 0.68$.


## Step 10
Therefore, the probability of a randomly selected person from this group visiting a physical therapist is $0.68$.

